er-Bridge copywriting framework. Both frameworks focus on transformation and growth, making them powerful tools for marketing personal development products or services.\n\nBy using the Coming of Age archetype, marketers can frame their product or service as a journey of self-discovery, where the customer will face challenges and obstacles, but ultimately emerge as a more confident and self-assured person. This creates a powerful narrative that speaks to the audience\'s desire for personal development and improvement.\n\nThen, by using the Before-After-Bridge framework, marketers can show the customer what their life will be like after using the product or service. This can create a sense of excitement and motivation that encourages the customer to take action and make a purchase.\n\nOverall, combining these two frameworks taps into a fundamental human desire for growth and transformation, and can create a compelling narrative that speaks to the audience\'s deepest aspirations.\nUser: Write me an email that I can use to announce this program to my list using "the Coming of Age story archetype and the Before-After-Bridge copywriting framework"\n\nmake it 750 words\nAssistant:', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=8, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1474, 25, 23643, 419, 25, 4710, 785, 39891, 315, 13081, 3364, 85157, 17601, 264, 3908, 45584, 879, 1969, 20876, 279, 11513, 315, 7826, 705, 323, 41587, 862, 1992, 304, 279, 1879, 13, 576, 13235, 12, 6025, 7671, 11183, 2975, 25304, 12626, 374, 6188, 311, 11167, 279, 17991, 429, 264, 1697, 646, 3139, 1283, 1667, 264, 1985, 476, 2473, 382, 785, 2874, 3170, 