INFO 06-17 10:20:50 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-64d20197edd04b9180f822c4289514ec-0: prompt: "User: How to get a job as a LMFT therapist in the US as an international student?\nAssistant: As an international student, there are a few extra steps that you will need to take in order to be able to work as a Licensed Marriage and Family Therapist (LMFT) in the United States. Here are some steps you can take to increase your chances of finding a job as an LMFT therapist:\n\n1. Obtain a student visa: In order to study in the United States, you will need to obtain a student visa. You can find more information about obtaining a student visa on the U.S. Department of State's website.\n2. Enroll in a graduate program in marriage and family therapy: In order to become an LMFT, you will need to complete a graduate-level program in marriage and family therapy that is accredited by the Commission on Accreditation for Marriage and Family Therapy Education (COAMFTE). You can find a list of COAMFTE-accredited programs on the American Association for Marriage and Family Therapy (AAMFT) website.\n3. Obtain a clinical internship: Many graduate programs in marriage and family therapy require students to complete a clinical internship as part of their coursework. This will give you the opportunity to gain hands-on experience working with clients and practicing therapy.\n4. Pass the licensure exam: Once you have completed your graduate program and clinical internship, you will need to pass the licensure exam in order to become an LMFT. The exam is administered by the Association of Marital and Family Therapy Regulatory Boards (AMFTRB).\n5. Find a job: After you have become an LMFT, you can start looking for job openings in your area. You may want to consider contacting local mental health clinics, hospitals, or private practices to see if they have any openings for LMFTs. You can also search for job openings on websites such as the AAMFT Job Connection or the National Council for Behavioral Health's Job Bank.\n\nI hope this information is helpful! If you have any other questions, don't hesitate to ask.\nUser: I am already enrolled in a graduate program so I have a student visa. How do I find jobs that offer H1B visa to international students as a therapist?\nAssistant: If you are an international student studying in the United States and you want to work as a therapist after you graduate, you will need to obtain a work visa. The H1B visa is a common choice for international students who want to work in the United States after completing their studies.\n\nTo apply for an H1B visa, you will need to have a job offer from an employer in the United States. The employer will need to sponsor your visa application and submit it to the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS).\n\nThere are a few steps you can take to increase your chances of finding a job that will sponsor your H1B visa:\n\n1. Look for job openings at companies that have sponsored H1B visas in the past: Some employers have a history of sponsoring H1B visas for international employees. You can check the Department of Labor's H1B Disclosure Data website to see which employers have sponsored H1B visas in the past.\n2. Network with professionals in your field: Attend job fairs and networking events in your field, and make connections with professionals who may be able to help you find a job.\n3. Consider working for a smaller company: Smaller companies may be more open to sponsoring H1B visas, as they may not have the same resources as larger companies to sponsor visas.\n4. Be proactive in your job search: Apply for jobs as soon as you see them advertised, and follow up with the employer to express your interest in the position.\n\nI hope this information is helpful! If you have any other questions, don't hesitate to ask.\nUser: Do you know of any companies that are known for sponsoring H1B for therapists?\nAssistant:", params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, fr