ment services and information online. The portal is a part of the e-governance initiatives of the Haryana government and aims to provide a transparent and efficient delivery of services to the citizens.\n\neDisha offers more than 100 services from various departments such as revenue, transport, food and supplies, and urban local bodies. These services include online applications for birth and death certificates, caste certificates, income certificates, and various other certificates, as well as services related to land records, driving licenses, and vehicle registration.\n\nThe eDisha portal allows citizens to apply for and track the status of their applications online, as well as make online payments for various services. The portal also provides information on government schemes, policies, and initiatives.\n\nApart from the online portal, eDisha has also set up e-Disha kendras at various locations in Haryana, including district headquarters, to provide citizens with assistance in using the portal and availing the services.\n\nIn summary, eDisha is a citizen-centric initiative of the Haryana government that aims to provide easy access to government services and information online. It has simplified the process of availing various services for citizens and has contributed to the efficient delivery of services in the state.\nUser: is edisha like system present in odissa\nAssistant:", params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=8, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1474, 25, 2980, 498, 4190, 1045, 1661, 384, 2371, 6706, 681, 27172, 304, 39389, 1582, 2216, 302, 315, 27711, 553, 9290, 8567, 198, 71703, 25, 261