INFO 06-17 10:21:01 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-3a043f11127048a482ec1248e6efcd78-0: prompt: "User: write an essay on french revolution\nAssistant: The French Revolution, which lasted from 1789 to 1799, was one of the most significant events in modern history. It was a period of radical social and political upheaval in France that had far-reaching consequences, not only for the country but for Europe and the world as a whole. This essay will explore the causes, key events, and outcomes of the French Revolution.\n\nCauses of the French Revolution\n\nThe French Revolution was a response to the economic, social, and political problems that had been building in France for decades. One of the main causes of the revolution was the country's deepening financial crisis. The French government was heavily in debt due to the cost of the Seven Years' War and the American Revolution, and the burden of this debt fell on the common people in the form of heavy taxes.\n\nAnother significant cause of the French Revolution was the country's outdated feudal system. The nobility and clergy held vast amounts of power and wealth, while the majority of the population, the peasants and middle class, were oppressed and excluded from political decision-making.\n\nKey Events of the French Revolution\n\nThe French Revolution can be divided into three distinct phases. The first phase, which lasted from 1789 to 1792, was marked by the establishment of the National Assembly, the fall of the Bastille, and the adoption of the Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen.\n\nThe second phase, which lasted from 1792 to 1794, was characterized by the rise of the radical Jacobin faction, led by Maximilien Robespierre. During this phase, the king, Louis XVI, was executed, and a Reign of Terror ensued, during which thousands of people were executed for perceived counter-revolutionary activities.\n\nThe third phase, which lasted from 1794 to 1799, saw the fall of Robespierre and the rise of the Directory, a five-man governing body. During this phase, the French armies expanded their control over Europe, but the country continued to experience political instability and economic problems.\n\nOutcomes of the French Revolution\n\nThe French Revolution had a profound impact on France and the world. In France, the Revolution brought an end to the monarchy and the feudal system, established the principles of liberty, equality, and fraternity, and created a modern, secular state.\n\nThe Revolution also had far-reaching effects on Europe and the world. It inspired similar revolutions in other countries, such as the Haitian Revolution, and helped to spread democratic ideas and values across the globe.\n\nConclusion\n\nThe French Revolution was a complex and multifaceted event that had profound consequences for France and the world. It was a response to economic, social, and political problems that had been building in France for decades and was marked by key events such as the establishment of the National Assembly, the fall of the Bastille, the execution of Louis XVI, and the Reign of Terror.\n\nThe Revolution's outcomes included the establishment of a modern, secular state in France and the spread of democratic ideas and values across the globe. Despite the challenges and controversies of the Revolution, it remains an important chapter in the history of the modern world.\nUser: put all the salient features in bullet format\nAssistant:", params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=8, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1474, 25, 3270, 458, 8895, 389, 41193, 13791, 198, 71703, 25, 576, 8585, 22126, 11, 8