INFO 06-17 10:21:13 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-1eb275af32f8412cab73e03a649b9e57-0: prompt: 'User: Write user stories that describe this concept in detail\nAssistant: Here are some user stories that describe the campaign feature in detail:\n\nAs a marketing manager, I want to create a campaign to promote a new product. I want to select a group of NFC objects that are associated with the product and include them in the campaign. I also want to specify a forward URL that users will be redirected to when they scan an NFC object. I want to be able to set a timeframe for the campaign and track the results in a dashboard so that I can see how many people are accessing the campaign and where they are located.\n\nAs a small business owner, I want to create a campaign to encourage customers to visit my store. I want to select a group of NFC objects that I will place around the store and include them in the campaign. I want to specify a forward URL that will provide customers with a special offer or discount when they scan an NFC object. I want to be able to run the campaign indefinitely so that it is always active for customers to participate in.\n\nAs a event organizer, I want to create a campaign to provide information about an upcoming event. I want to select a group of NFC objects that will be distributed at the event and include them in the campaign. I want to specify a forward URL that will provide users with details about the event, including the schedule, location, and other important information. I want to be able to set a specific timeframe for the campaign so that it is only active during the event.\n\nAs a campaign administrator, I want to ensure that no NFC object is included in two campaigns at the same time. I want to be able to see which objects are included in each campaign and prevent any conflicts. I also want to be able to review the results of completed campaigns in the dashboard so that I can see how successful they were and make informed decisions about future campaigns.\nUser: Write a tl;dr of the campaigns concept\nAssistant: "Campaigns" is a feature in a web application that allows users to create targeted marketing or promotion efforts using NFC technology. When an NFC object associated with a campaign is scanned, the end-user is redirected to a specific forward URL. Users can configure a set of NFC objects to be included in the campaign by specifying a list of tags and can choose to run the campaign within a specific timeframe or indefinitely. The results of the campaign, including the number of scanned objects and the locations of the scans, can be visualized in a dashboard. The dashboard can be used to monitor the progress of ongoing campaigns or review the results of completed campaigns.\nUser: Please write a shorter summary\nAssistant: "Campaigns" is a feature in a web application that allows users to create targeted marketing efforts using NFC technology. Users can configure a set of NFC objects and a forward URL for each campaign and track the results in a dashboard. Campaigns can be run within a specific timeframe or indefinitely.\nUser: Write a user story for unarchiving archived campaigns that have completed or were manually archived\nAssistant: Here is a user story for unarchiving archived campaigns:\n\nAs a marketing manager, I want to be able to unarchive campaigns that have completed or were manually archived so that I can review their results or reuse them in the future. I want to be able to access the dashboard and see a list of all archived campaigns, including those that have completed and those that were manually archived. I want to be able to select an archived campaign and unarchive it, which should make it active again and allow me to review or edit the details. I also want to be able to see the status of each campaign (active, archived, completed) so that I can easily differentiate between them.\nUser: Add acceptance criteria to the user story\nAssistant:', params: SamplingParam