s and traditional cooking techniques.\n2. Isshisoden Nakamura: This restaurant is located in the Arashiyama area and offers kaiseki ryori courses starting from around 7,000 yen per person. They use locally sourced ingredients and offer vegetarian options.\n3. Gion Suetomo: This restaurant is located in the Gion district and offers kaiseki ryori courses starting from around 6,000 yen per person. They are known for their simple yet elegant dishes and relaxing atmosphere.\n4. Yudofu Sagano: This restaurant is located in the Sagano area and offers a unique kaiseki ryori experience centered around yudofu, a type of tofu dish. Courses start from around 4,000 yen per person.\n\nThese are just a few options to consider, and there are many other affordable kaiseki ryori restaurants in Kyoto. It's always best to research and compare different options based on your preferences and budget to find the one that suits you best.\nUser: yakitori at Torito price\nAssistant: Torito is a popular yakitori (grilled chicken skewers) restaurant in Kyoto that offers a variety of delicious and affordable dishes. The prices may vary depending on the menu items you order, but here are some examples of the prices for their yakitori dishes:\n\n* Chicken skewers (thigh, breast, liver, etc.): 120-150 yen per skewer\n* Vegetables (asparagus, shiitake mushrooms, eggplant, etc.): 120-150 yen per skewer\n* Special dishes (chicken meatball, chicken wings, etc.): 200-350 yen per skewer\n\nThey also offer set menus that include a variety of yakitori and side dishes, which cost around 1,500 to 2,500 yen per person.\n\nPlease note that the prices may be subject to change and do not include any drinks or additional menu items. It's always best to check the restaurant's website or ask the staff for the up-to-date prices and menu options.\nUser: kakinoha-zushi at Nakatanidou price\nAssistant:", params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, to