 a measure of the standard deviation of the errors.\n\nRMSE = √[(1/n) \\* Σ(y\\_exp - y\\_calc)^2]\n\n1. Coefficient of Determination (R-squared)\nThe coefficient of determination (R-squared) measures the proportion of the variance in the experimental values that can be explained by the calculated values. It gives a measure of the goodness of fit of the calculated values to the experimental data.\n\nR-squared = 1 - (Σ(y\\_exp - y\\_calc)^2 / Σ(y\\_exp - ȳ)^2)\n\nwhere ȳ is the mean of the experimental values.\n\nThese measures can be used individually or in combination to assess the accuracy of the calculated values compared to the experimental data.\nUser: the values I am trying to compare are a series of lens power calculated theoretically and another series of values that were calculated using ray tracing software\nAssistant: To compare a series of theoretical lens powers with another series of lens powers calculated using ray tracing software, you can use the statistical measures I mentioned in the previous response.\n\nFor example, you can calculate the mean absolute error (MAE) between the two series of values as follows:\n\n1. Calculate the absolute difference between each theoretical value and the corresponding ray tracing value.\n2. Take the average of the absolute differences to get the mean absolute error.\n\nMAE = (1/n) \\* Σ|P\\_theo - P\\_rt|\n\nwhere P\\_theo is the theoretical lens power, P\\_rt is the lens power obtained from ray tracing software, and n is the total number of values being compared.\n\nSimilarly, you can calculate the root mean squared error (RMSE) and coefficient of determination (R-squared) to assess the difference between the two series of values.\n\nRMSE = √[(1/n) \\* Σ(P\\_theo - P\\_rt)^2]\n\nR-squared = 1 - (Σ(P\\_theo - P\\_rt)^2 / Σ(P\\_theo - ȳ)^2)\n\nwhere ȳ is the mean of the theoretical lens powers.\n\nThese measures can help you assess the accuracy of the ray tracing software in calculating the lens power compared to the theoretical values.\nUser: how can I interpret the value of MAE?\nAssistant:", params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=8, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1474, 25, 1246, 646, 358, 11047, 279, 1465, 1948, 264, 4013, 315, 2750, 16588, 6888, 336, 7022, 448, 2441, 9342, 745, 198, 71703, 25, 2014, 11047, 279, 1465, 1948, 264, 4013, 315, 2750, 16588, 6888, 336, 7022, 323, 2441, 9342, 745, 11, 498, 646, 990, 279, 2701, 14806, 369, 37614, 279, 3266, 1465, 1447, 24422, 1465, 284, 320, 91, 86703, 897, 481, 31787, 897, 91, 608, 31787, 897, 8, 856, 220, 16, 15, 15, 15441, 9064, 279, 22000, 897, 374, 279, 897, 12180, 1526, 65096, 11, 279, 31787, 897, 374, 279, 897, 12180, 1526, 35972, 21937, 11, 323, 279, 10740, 897, 374, 4429, 311, 5978, 429, 279, 1465, 374, 2677, 6785, 382, 2461, 3110, 11, 1077, 594, 1977, 498, 16588, 279, 31787, 897, 369, 458, 9342, 311, 387, 220, 16, 15, 11, 714, 279, 22000, 897, 498, 12180, 572, 220, 24, 13, 20, 13, 1446, 646, 11047, 279, 3266, 1465, 438, 11017, 1447, 24422, 1465, 284, 320, 91, 24, 13, 20, 481, 220, 16, 15, 91, 608, 220, 16, 15, 8, 856, 220, 16, 15, 15, 13744, 24422, 1465, 284, 320, 15, 13, 20, 608, 220, 16, 15, 8, 856, 220, 16, 15, 15, 13744, 24422, 1465, 284, 220, 20, 15441, 1986, 3363, 429, 279, 22000, 897, 702, 458, 1465, 315, 220, 20, 4, 7707, 311, 279, 31787, 897, 624, 1474, 25, 358, 614, 264, 4013, 315, 2750, 311, 9429, 11, 537, 1101, 825, 897, 13, 1128, 6629, 646, 358, 990, 5267, 71703, 25, 1416, 498, 614, 264, 4013, 315, 2750, 311, 9429, 11, 498, 646, 990, 28464, 10953, 1741, 438, 279, 3076, 10740, 1465, 320, 4835, 36, 701, 3704, 3076, 52263, 1465, 320, 23652, 92