INFO 06-17 10:21:29 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-4d7677c8e6214aac9f5a46dafbbf8e49-0: prompt: 'User: I am in last year of industrial engineering and I am currently looking for a 6 month internship. Here is the description of an offer where I have the final interview the 8 march. The offer : \nBusiness Analyst Intern\nIdentifiant du poste: 2239821 | Amazon EU SARL\n\nDESCRIPTION\nAn Amazon internship will provide you with an unforgettable experience in an international environment; it will boost your resume and will provide a superb introduction to our company.\n\nWe are seeking motivated Business Analysis Interns to join our available roles in the following teams: Supply Chain, Network Planning, Inventory Placement, Transportation, Last Mile, Finance, Planning & Analysis, or Finance & Controlling.\n\nAbout this Internship\n\nWhatever your background is, if you love gathering large amounts of data and identifying trends that the business can act upon to reduce cost and/or improve efficiency; and if you are motivated by results and are driven to achieve them, this internship could be a great opportunity for you. By coming up with new ideas and challenging the status quo we can continue to be the most customer-centric company on Earth. We are all about flexibility and we encourage you to embrace the challenge.\n\nYou will test your analytical and technical skills. This internship is a learning opportunity, where you will put your skills and bias for action to the test, to complete a project that will support your own growth in the Business Analysis function, as well as the team and our customers success. This could include:\n\n· Learning how to partner across multiple teams and geographies\n· Developing and executing complex data analyses, which will in turn drive the correct business decisions\n· Helping identify process improvement opportunities to build streamlined and scalable solutions\n· Partnering with the team to perform root cause analyses when facing problems\n· Assisting in the development of business cases for new programs and services\n· Participating in the development, delivery, maintenance and improvement of performance metrics dashboards\n· Becoming part of a team of trusted advisors throughout an entire business unit\n\nRECRUITMENT PROCESS\nThe first stage, is an online assessment that you will receive when you apply for the role. This assessment takes around 45 minutes. After this, if successful you will move through to the final stage, which is a panel interview with Amazonians. If necessary you may also have to complete a language test.\nQUALIFICATIONS DE BASE\nBasic qualifications We want to hire the most talented people and offer them an environment in which they can relentlessly improve our customer experience. · You are currently working towards a 2+ years university degree in Business Analytics, Finance, Accounting, Economics, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, Supply Chain, Logistics or a similar discipline · You must have the right to work in the country of employment by the start date · Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel (e.g. macros, pivots, lookups, VBA) · Proficiency in SQL/ETL · Fluent English (both spoken and written) · Highly analytical, detail-oriented and an understanding of business · Ability to develop new ideas, creative solutions and demonstrated experience in successful implementing them · Results driven, with the ability to innovate and simplify processes and practices\nQUALIFICATIONS APPRÉCIÉES\nPreferred qualifications · Any additional technical skills, such as coding (e.g. Python, R, Django), data visualization (e.g. Tableau, QlikView, PowerPivot, MicroStrategy) or operations research · Familiar with Oracle and/or any AWS products (e.g. Redshift, EMR) · Previous work experience – a summer job, internship; if it’s an experience in a related field or business, even better · Any additional related technical competence, would be considered as a plus.\nAmazon is an equal opportunities employer. We believe passionately that employing a diverse workforce is central to our success. We make recruiting decisions based on your experience and skills. We value your passion to discover, invent, simplify and build. Protecting your privacy and the security of your data is a longstanding top priority for Amazon. Please consult our Privacy Notice (https://www.amazon.jobs/en/privacy\\_page) to know more about how we collect, use and transfer the personal data of our candidates.\n\nPlease write in English language.\nAssistant:', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=8, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1474, 25, 358, 1079, 304, 1537, 1042, 315, 12785, 14667, 323, 358, 1079, 5023, 3330, 369, 264, 220, 21, 2254, 59759, 13, 5692, 374, 279, 4008, 315, 458, 3010, 1380, 358, 614, 279, 1590, 7128, 279, 220, 23, 15217, 13, 576, 3010, 549, 715, 22727, 40470, 4414, 198, 28301, 83454, 3845, 91046, 25, 220, 17, 17, 18, 24, 23, 17, 16, 760, 8176, 9812, 68778, 43, 271, 45433, 198, 2082, 8176, 59759, 686, 3410, 498, 448, 458, 59998, 3139, 304, 458, 6489, 4573, 26, 432, 686, 7760, 697, 15688, 323, 686, 3410, 264, 32589, 16800, 311, 1039, 2813, 382, 1654, 525, 10887, 26664, 8025, 18320, 4414, 82, 311, 5138, 1039, 2500, 12783, 304, 279, 2701, 7263, 25, 29809, 28525, 11, 8141, 27680, 11, 28126, 77416, 11, 29878, 11, 7996, 38597, 11, 22453, 11, 27680, 609, 18320, 11, 476, 22453, 609, 2093, 16210, 382, 10494, 419, 4414, 5270, 271, 46816, 697, 4004, 374, 11, 421, 498, 2948, 22888, 3460, 14713, 315, 821, 323, 24588, 18339, 429, 279, 2562, 646, 1160, 5193, 311, 7949, 27