on should summarize relevant literature and evidence related to the healthcare problem being addressed. DNP students should include a description of the search strategy used to identify relevant literature, as well as a synthesis of the key findings and recommendations. The literature review should be properly cited using APA 7th edition. A grading rubric for the literature review section can include the following:\n\n| Section | Description | Points |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Search Strategy | Description of the search strategy used to identify relevant literature. | 10 points |\n| Key Findings | Synthesis of key findings and recommendations from relevant literature. | 60 points |\n| APA 7th Edition | Proper use of APA 7th edition for in-text citations, references, and formatting. | 30 points |\n\nOverall, the rubric emphasizes the importance of a systematic and evidence-based approach to needs assessment, including the identification of clear goals, the gathering and analysis of data from multiple sources, and the development of a comprehensive plan of action based on the findings of the assessment.\nUser: Can you organize this section and cite roy brown Clinical Inquiry Question Development Checklist\nRoy E. Brown\nAssistant:", params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=8, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [71703, 25, 22555, 0, 5692, 594, 264, 10273, 2216, 369, 264, 3880, 15449, 3118, 389, 279, 16170, 32640, 304, 576, 18635, 315, 45253, 26984, 75160, 553, 1863, 4475, 3246, 6591, 323, 5807, 1447, 91, 11113, 760, 7662, 760, 20725, 9248, 91, 12448, 760, 12448, 760, 12448, 9248, 91, 34920, 323, 29045, 760, 