on should summarize relevant literature and evidence related to the healthcare problem being addressed. DNP students should include a description of the search strategy used to identify relevant literature, as well as a synthesis of the key findings and recommendations. The literature review should be properly cited using APA 7th edition. A grading rubric for the literature review section can include the following:\n\n| Section | Description | Points |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Search Strategy | Description of the search strategy used to identify relevant literature. | 10 points |\n| Key Findings | Synthesis of key findings and recommendations from relevant literature. | 60 points |\n| APA 7th Edition | Proper use of APA 7th edition for in-text citations, references, and formatting. | 30 points |\n\nOverall, the rubric emphasizes the importance of a systematic and evidence-based approach to needs assessment, including the identification of clear goals, the gathering and analysis of data from multiple sources, and the development of a comprehensive plan of action based on the findings of the assessment.\nUser: Can you organize this section and cite roy brown Clinical Inquiry Question Development Checklist\nRoy E. Brown\nAssistant: Sure, here's a revised version of the Feasibility section organized and citing Roy E. Brown's Clinical Inquiry Question Development Checklist:\n\nFeasibility\n\na. Clinical Inquiry Question Development Checklist (Brown, 2014)\ni. Is the clinical inquiry question feasible and relevant to the practice setting?\nii. Is the clinical inquiry question grounded in an understanding of the current literature?\niii. Is the clinical inquiry question answerable through the collection of empirical data?\niv. Is the clinical inquiry question significant to the nursing profession?\nv. Is the clinical inquiry question important to the health and well-being of patients?\n\nb. SWOT Analysis\ni. Conduct a SWOT analysis of the site to assess the feasibility of implementing a project. You may use a table for the analysis.\nii. Determine if the problem or issue is within the scope of nursing practice. If not, consider teaming up with those who are part of the clinical practice or choosing a different topic.\niii. Identify which hospital patient safety goal or initiative aligns with the problem or issue. Be specific.\niv. Evaluate how much time is needed to explore the topic through implementation and if the team has enough time to dedicate to it. Consider partnering with hospital resources or teams to maximize time.\nv. Assess if the organization has the necessary resources, such as tests and equipment, to implement the intervention.\nvi. Estimate the costs of the practice change and potential cost savings for the organization to determine the return on investment.\n\nReference:\nBrown, R. E. (2014). Clinical inquiry question development checklist. In D. M. White & S. A. Dudley-Brown (Eds.), Translation of evidence into nursing and health care (2nd ed., pp. 20-21). Springer Publishing Company.\nUser: Can you describe each category and give requirements\nAssistant:", params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=8, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [71703, 25, 22555, 0, 5692, 594, 264, 10273, 2216, 369, 264, 3880, 15449, 3118, 389, 279, 16170, 32640, 304, 576, 18635, 315, 45253, 26984, 75160, 553, 1863, 4475, 3246, 6591, 323, 5807, 1447, 91, 11113, 760, 7662, 760, 20725, 9248, 91, 12448, 760, 12448, 760, 12448, 9248, 91, 34920, 323, 29045, 760, 12023, 7271, 315, 6891, 323, 7428, 315, 279, 3880, 15449, 429, 5285, 82, 448, 2390, 8845, 323, 25398, 13, 760, 220, 17, 15, 3